<p>KYC, or Know Your Customer, is a process that verifies the identity of individuals engaging in Binance Coin transactions. This helps prevent fraudulent activities and ensures a secure environment for users.</p>



<p>By implementing KYC standards, Binance Coin can effectively manage risk and compliance. KYC procedures involve collecting and verifying personal information, such as identification documents, to confirm the identity of users.</p>



<p>It allows Binance Coin to comply with legal requirements and maintain a trusted and compliant platform. By prioritizing KYC in Binance Coin transactions, the platform ensures secure transactions and protects both users and the integrity of the cryptocurrency ecosystem.</p>



